> Why enable this by default? I think it has not been fully tested.

At present, the latest version of flink doris connector is submitted in 2pc mode to ensure the exactly once semantics of doris storage. We have done a lot of tests based on this, and there is no problem at present, so we hope that from the 1.1 version of doris, this configuration will be turned on by default.
On the other hand, even if this configuration is enabled by default, it has no effect on the normal streamload, because the 2pc streamload also needs to be displayed in the header to declare that 2pc is enabled
Ready for reviewing now

If it has been tested, I think we can merge this into 1.1. So that we can match the new version of flink-connector in next release.

create table apply_info_v3
(
    id           bigint default '0' comment '自增',

    update_month char(7)     default ''                    comment '更新时间所在月',
    update_week  char(8)     default ''                    comment '更新时间所在周',
    update_day   char(10)    default ''                    comment '更新时间所在天',
